Filter genotypes, wecare feb2016

Alexey Larionov

started: 01Mar2016 last updated: 12May2016

Notes

It was discussed with DC whether to filter cases by call rate per case. There was ~3 cases with low coverage (<20) and low call rates (<50%). We desided to keep such cases because their retained genotypes still passed all filters.

Instead of setting the thresholds by the proportions of reads (as done in this script), it is possible to set thresholds by probability of the observed reads. This could be dome using pbinom(count of minor reads, sum of reads, 0.5). The used proportion thresholds correspond to 1-5%, depending on total reads count.

Thresholds for min DP and GQ were set to 10 and 20 because they are commonly used (e.g.see Carson BMC Bioinformatics 2014 15:125).

A small number of genotypes (~0.01%) was covered too high to be true (up to 1-2k coverage). These are obvious mistakes, and they have been removed too. Arbitrary the threshold for max DP was set to 500 (~10 x Average Coverage).
